Installation:

- Create a mySQL database and execute as mysql admin:

  mysql> CREATE DATABASE phtagr;
  mysql> GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON phtagr.* TO 'phtagr'@'localhost' \
      IDENTIFIED BY '<PASSWD>'; 

- Checkout the new branch from svn to a webbrowser directory like
  ~/.public_html or /var/www

  $ svn checkout svn://inspirationslos.de/phtagr/trunk/phtagr

- Change to the phtagr directory

- Create a subdirectory cache which is writeable by the webserver. Eg.

  $ chmod 777 cache

  mysql> CREATE DATABASE sebastian;
  mysql> GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON sebastian.* TO 'sebastian'@'localhost'
  IDENTIFIED BY '<PASSWD>'; or better
 
  $ chgrp www-data cache
  $ chmod 774 cache

- change the write permission of the subdirectory temporarily

  $ chmod 777 phtagr

- run setup.php
  - Enter the mysql data
  - Create admin account (account name must be "admin")

- Change the permission of subdirectory phtagr to read only
  
  $ chmod 755 phtagr

- Change the permission of setup.php to not readable.

  $ chmod 600 phtagr

- Run index.php
  - To add images, login as admin and browse the filesystem.

